# V3Code Build Rules

## Which build command to use

| What you changed | Command | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `.tsx` / `.css` in `react/src/` | `.\dev.ps1 -Once` | Fast (~15s). Ctrl+R reloads UI. |
| `.ts` in `browser/` or `common/` | `.\dev.ps1 -FullGulp` | Full compile (~3 min). Ctrl+R reloads. |
| `.ts` in `electron-main/` | `.\dev.ps1 -FullGulp` + full restart | Main process loads code ONCE at launch. Ctrl+R does NOT reload main process. |

## Common mistakes that waste time

1. **Editing `electron-main/*.ts` and running `-Once`** — the fast path only builds the React bundle. Your changes won't compile.
2. **Editing `electron-main/*.ts`, running `-FullGulp`, then only doing Ctrl+R** — main process keeps OLD code in memory. Must fully quit and relaunch V3Code.
3. **Editing `common/prompt/prompts.ts` or `browser/toolsService.ts` and running `-Once`** — these are NOT in the React bundle. Need `-FullGulp`.

## Rule of thumb

If the file is under `void/browser/react/src/` → fast path works.
Everything else under `void/` → needs `-FullGulp`.
